The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, March 01, 2004 				 Girl sold in Punjab rescued 
																								Calcutta, Feb. 29: Sixteen-year-old Ruksana Khatoon, sold to a businessman in Punjab for Rs 15,000, was rescued yesterday.																								Three people, including the businessman, Tarsem Singh, have been arrested. Singh was picked up from Punjab. Ruksanas husband Kalimullah Laskar, who had allegedly sold her, and Mursalin Laskar were arrested from Diamond Harbour on January 13 on the basis of a complaint filed the previous day by the girls mother Rizia Bibi. 																								Rizia had suspected Kalimullah after he started coming to his in-laws house without Ruksana. The police traced the girl after she managed to call home.
